      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 307: onPushReceived() mutates pushWakeLock and pushEventDisposable from push service coroutine threads without synchronization. Concurrent Firebase/UnifiedPush deliveries can race, create duplicate subscriptions, overwrite a wakelock reference, or release a wakelock while another thread is acquiring it. Run all push-hold state transitions on the main thread or protect them with a single lock.\n```suggestion\nprivate val pushStateLock \u003d Any()\n\nfun onPushReceived() \u003d synchronized(pushStateLock) {\n    cancelIdleShutdown()\n    activePushCount.incrementAndGet()\n    ...\n}\n\nprivate fun releasePushHold() \u003d synchronized(pushStateLock) {\n    ...\n}\n```",
