      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 393: The wakelock release swallows all exceptions, including the common case where the wakelock has already timed out and is no longer held. This hides lifecycle bugs and makes push wake failures hard to diagnose. Check isHeld before release and log unexpected failures.\n```suggestion\npushWakeLock?.let { wakeLock -\u003e\n    try {\n        if (wakeLock.isHeld) wakeLock.release()\n    } catch (e: RuntimeException) {\n        Log.w(TAG, \"Failed to release push wakelock\", e)\n    }\n}\npushWakeLock \u003d null\n```",
