      "message": "[Major] Line 401: releasePushHold() calls startForegroundService() only to deliver ACTION_PUSH_DONE. On Android O+, starting a new foreground service from the background can be restricted; if the original service already timed out or failed to start, this completion signal may throw and leave cleanup dependent on logs. Prefer stopping an already-running service via a normal startService/bind-safe path, or make PushForegroundService self-stop from the same start lifecycle without requiring a new background FGS launch.\n```suggestion\ntry {\n    startService(Intent(this, PushForegroundService::class.java)\n        .setAction(PushForegroundService.ACTION_PUSH_DONE))\n} catch (e: Exception) {\n    Log.w(TAG, \"Can\u0027t signal push done to foreground service\", e)\n}\n```",
